Vice President Biden will be speaking at a legal symposium celebrating the 15th anniversary of the Violence Against Women Act (VAWA). The event will take place at Georgetown University Law Center on April 22nd. Biden will receive The Legal Momentum Hero Award for his role in initiating and championing the VAWA. The Vice President will give remarks at the symposium. The event is open to the press, but RSVP is required. For more information, contact the Georgetown University Law Center.